    "content": [
        {
            "id": "block-001",
            "tag": "h1",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "TaskUtil"
        },
        {
            "id": "block-002",
            "tag": "p",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "`TaskUtil` is a small set of controls for **background tasks** — work that runs alongside your game rather than all at once. It lets you start a task and stop one or all of them."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-003",
            "tag": "table",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "headers": [
                "Method",
                "What it does"
            ],
            "rows": [
                ["`Start()`", "Begins a background task."],
                ["`Stop()`", "Stops the current task."],
                ["`StopAll()`", "Stops every running task."]
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "block-004",
            "tag": "note",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "For most everyday timing needs, you'll get further with the tools you already know: schedule a one-off action with [Utility's CallMethodDelayed](/docs/uniscript/en-us/utility#block-004), and handle per-frame or repeating timing with [Time](/docs/uniscript/en-us/time)."
        },
        {
            "id": "block-005",
            "tag": "h2",
            "styles": null,
            "classes": null,
            "text": "Full method reference"
        },
        {
